name>Col d'Izoard (2,360 m)</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>6.735000,44.820000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Guillestre</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>6.651000,44.661000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Col de Vars (2,109 m)</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>6.702700,44.540000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Barcelonnette</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>6.650500,44.387700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Col de la Cayolle (2,326 m)</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>6.743000,44.262000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Saint-Martin-Vésubie</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>7.253000,44.070000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Col de Turini (1,607 m)</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>7.403500,43.992300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Sospel</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>7.453300,43.877200,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Col de l'Iseran</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[2,770 m, highest paved pass in the Alps. Stone chapel on the summit. The road usually opens last week of June; on bad-snow years not until mid-July.]]></description><Point><coordinates>7.031200,45.417000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Bonneval-sur-Arc</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Listed among 'most beautiful villages of France' — slate-roofed stone houses, no concrete, no overhead wires. Glacier source of the Arc river just upstream.]]></description><Point><coordinates>7.039800,45.376000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Col du Galibier</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[2,645 m. Most-climbed pass in Tour de France history. Henri Desgrange monument; the riders pass it with their hats off in homage.]]></description><Point><coordinates>6.407000,45.064000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Briançon</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Highest fortified town in the Alps (1,326 m); Vauban's 1690s star fortress is intact and UNESCO-listed.]]></description><Point><coordinates>6.641100,44.899000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Col d'Izoard / Casse Déserte</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[2,360 m. Just below the summit on the south side, the 'Casse Déserte' — a moonscape of orange-yellow scree pinnacles. Tour de France climbing legend.]]></description><Point><coordinates>6.735000,44.820000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Col de Turini</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[1,607 m. Used in the Monte Carlo Rally for decades — every rally driver in Europe has crashed somewhere on its hairpins. Now in summer just a beautiful beech-forest pass.]]></description><Point><coordinates>7.403500,43.992300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
</Document></kml>
